  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vocabulary size is a foundational tokenizer hyperparameter that trades off sequence length, model memory, subword granularity, and handling of rare text. Choosing 32K versus 128K tokens affects embedding matrix size, inference speed, and how efficiently an agent's prompts compress — especially for code, JSON, and multilingual workloads."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vocabulary size is the number of unique tokens in a tokenizer's dictionary, including special tokens. It determines the embedding matrix rows (vocab_size × embed_dim parameters) and the output logits dimension. Larger vocabularies encode common words as single tokens (shorter sequences) but increase memory and compute per softmax step."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agent cost and context capacity scale with token count, which depends on vocabulary efficiency. A 100K vocabulary might encode English prose in 30% fewer tokens than a 32K vocabulary, fitting more RAG context — but the embedding and output layers grow proportionally. Domain-specific agents (code, biology) may need vocabularies trained on domain corpora for efficient tokenization."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Larger vocab: shorter sequences",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — fewer tokens for common words and phrases"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Smaller vocab: smaller model",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — less embedding and lm_head memory"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Domain-tuned vocab",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — efficient encoding of jargon, APIs, identifiers"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Tunable at training time",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — merge count set during tokenizer training"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Embedding parameters scale O(vocab_size × embed_dim) — large vocabs bloat small models"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Softmax over huge vocabularies slows inference (mitigated by sampling and optimized kernels)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Very large vocabs may include rare tokens with poorly trained embeddings"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cannot change vocabulary size post-training without retraining embeddings and output layer"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "During BPE/SentencePiece training, merge operations stop at target vocabulary size. Common sizes: GPT-2 (50,257), Llama 2 (32,000), Llama 3 (128,256), GPT-4 (estimated ~100K)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from transformers import AutoConfig\n\nfor name in [\"gpt2\", \"meta-llama/Llama-3.2-1B\", \"google/gemma-2-2b\"]:\n    try:\n        cfg = AutoConfig.from_pretrained(name)\n        print(f\"{name}: vocab_size={cfg.vocab_size}\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"{name}: skipped ({e})\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Compare token efficiency for the same agent prompt across models:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import tiktoken\nfrom transformers import AutoTokenizer\n\ntext = open(\"sample_agent_prompt.txt\").read()\n\ngpt4_enc = tiktoken.encoding_for_model(\"gpt-4o\")\nllama_tok = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"meta-llama/Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct\")\n\nprint(\"GPT-4o tokens:\", len(gpt4_enc.encode(text)))\nprint(\"Llama 3.2 tokens:\", len(llama_tok.encode(text)))"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use it"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Consider vocabulary efficiency when selecting base models for token-budget-constrained agents. Train custom tokenizers with appropriate vocabulary size when building domain-specific models from scratch. Do not attempt to resize vocabulary of released models without full retraining."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Examples"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A 32K vocabulary model tokenizes \"implementation\" as [\"implement\", \"ation\"] (2 tokens); a larger vocabulary with that merge may use 1 token. Code with many short identifiers benefits less from large English-optimized vocabularies unless code was included in merge training."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-world example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A code-review agent switched from a 32K general model to a 100K code-heavy vocabulary model. Average review prompt dropped from 6,800 to 5,100 tokens — allowing 25% more file context in the same 8K window without changing the context limit."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Choosing models by parameter count alone without comparing token efficiency on representative prompts"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Assuming larger vocabulary is always better — memory and softmax costs rise"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Attempting vocabulary extension on pretrained models without re-initializing new token embeddings"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Benchmark token counts on real agent prompts, not generic prose"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Balance vocabulary size with model size budget for edge deployments"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Include domain text in custom tokenizer training corpora when building specialized models"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Track tokens-per-request as a first-class metric alongside latency and cost"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Comparison with alternatives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Character-level vocabularies (~256 bytes) minimize embedding rows but maximize sequence length. Word-level vocabularies (100K+ words) minimize sequence length for known words but fail on OOV. Subword vocabularies (32K–128K) are the practical LLM sweet spot. Mixture-of-tokenizers (e.g., byte fallback) adds flexibility at complexity cost."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mental model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vocabulary size is the dictionary thickness — a thicker dictionary uses shorter sentences (fewer tokens) but weighs more to carry (larger embedding matrix)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Vocabulary size affects token count, embedding memory, and softmax compute"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Typical LLM vocabularies range from 32K to 128K subword tokens"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Compare token efficiency on domain-specific agent prompts when choosing models"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Vocabulary is fixed at training time — cannot resize without retraining"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
